cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.DB

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract information from scientific text. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of machine learning models for classification tasks also suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the use of large-scale data processing and database management for PubMed abstracts extraction indicates the possibility of it belonging to cs.DB (Databases).
